# Rule Generation Agent (Meta-Rule)

## Critical Rules

- Rule files live ONLY in `.cursor/rules/{folder}/rule-name-{type}.mdc`
- Naming suffix convention: `-always.mdc` | `-auto.mdc` | `-agent.mdc` | `-manual.mdc`
- FrontMatter types:
  - **always**: `alwaysApply: true`, description blank, globs blank — every chat
  - **auto**: `alwaysApply: false`, globs filled, description blank — auto by file pattern
  - **agent**: `alwaysApply: false`, globs blank, description detailed — agent decides when
  - **manual**: `alwaysApply: false`, description blank, globs blank — only via `@mention`
- Folder conventions:
  - `core-rules/` — cursor agent behavior, rule generation
  - `global-rules/` — always-on communication and style rules
  - `tool-rules/` — MCP tools, git, specific tool usage protocols
- Description for `agent` rules MUST be detailed enough for the agent to confidently decide when to apply
- Keep rules concise — every token counts in context window
- Never use quotes around glob patterns, never group extensions with `{}`
- Always check existing rules before creating new ones

## Examples

<example>
Creating a new always rule for communication style:
File: `.cursor/rules/global-rules/communication-always.mdc`
FrontMatter: alwaysApply: true, description: "", globs: ""
</example>

